inn1.comm: and Fletcher gives away a bye first ball. It stayed low a touch after Masakadza left it alone, but was a regulation take by international standards
variable bounce? this one nips back in and gets Sibanda in the chest. His arms are shouldered already, and he is surprised with the extra bounce
superb pull shot, gets stuck into another short delivery, pulling it in front of square. Cracking shot, good morning, Roach
angled into the pads, and helped away for a single to fine leg

silly running and good work by Roach, out goes Sibanda! Masakadza has dropped this one at his feet, and is called through by Sibanda, but Roach is quick, gets a good bounce, and flicks a direct hit before the Sibanda dive can get him in. Poor call for the run so early on
is beaten by the inward movement, the ball rolls off the pad
left alone outside off by Masakadza, just short of a length
hint of inswing, on target, and defended towards on
short and way outside off, called wide
saved by the too much swing here! surprises the batsman with both the swing and pace, good shout, but sliding down the leg side
saved by the inside edge this time, this one is bowled from closer to the stumps, and beats him with the inswing, and is headed for the stumps, but there is a slight inside edge
too straight this time, and he gets a tickle off the thigh
flicked but straight to midwicket, ends a good over that contained tow big lbw shouts
digs this one in short, Taylor looking to leave it, but fends at it late, yet manages to keep it down
lunges forward and leaves it alone, almost Ponting-style

has Nikita Miller made mess of this one? Taylor upper-cuts, Miller at third man runs in, and realises he would have taken it shoulder high had he stayed on the rope. Counts as a drop, but the scorebook will say six runs
turns this off the pads for a single to fine leg
opens the face on this one, can't get it past backward point
short, tucks him up, defended
short of a length, wide outside off, left alone by Taylor
gets shape back in towards the batsman, but not close enough to the off stump to bother Taylor
another lbw shout, Taylor's bat is hidden behind the pad, and half the ball has hit him in line of off stump. Simon Taufel gives him the benefit of doubt!
outside off, not swinging this time, and left alone
wide outside off again, Taylor covers the stumps, and leaves it alone
defended off the front foot, maiden over
short, into the ribs, defended towards mid-on
fuller, outside off, looks to drive but doesn't connect sweetly
length ball, around off, hit back one bounce to Roach
finally Masakadza gets off the mark, pushes this just wide of mid-off and comes through for one
back of a length, on off, defended to cover
fuller, around off again, Taylor defends off the front foot
just back of a length, hit to cover
and Masakdaza breaks the shackles, dances down the track, and drives it wide of mid-off - along the ground
jumps out of the crease again, Bernard goes full and wide and beats him
this is a very nice shot, steps out of the crease again, but gets outside the line and plays across the line, along the ground, and past midwicket
runs this one down to third man

edged wide of first slip, and almost runs himself out running the second! this one doesn't swing in and he ends up playing inside the line, and the thick edge flies past the only slip. Taylor comes back for the second, but is surprised by Barath's slide and whipped throw, and Taylor has to put in a full-length lunge to save himself
dug in short, Masakadza makes a late decision to go for the upper cut, and is late into it. One bouncer for the over
beautiful shot, shimmies down the pitch, turns this into an over-pitched delivery, and he lets it to come on to the bat and flicks it late and past midwicket
shorter, outside off, is drawn into the shot, but plays inside the line
crispy shot! powerfully hit but back to Roach

soft dismissal! gets under a short delivery and upper-cuts, but doesn't put much power into the shot, just helps it along, and it ends up down Nikita Miller's throat at third man. Roach is kicked, does a windmill celebration, and kisses the West Indies badge on his shirt
defends the first delivery off the front foot
around off, length delivery, defended
wide of off, and left alone
thrown up wide, and he drives with an open face, and gets it past a diving Pollard at backward point
bunts this shortish delivery into the leg side, and comes through for one
short and wide, guided away to third man for a single
square-drive, good looking shot! short and wide, leans back and drives it past cover
dug in short again, and Taibu looks to cut and is beaten by the bounce
fuller, but still manages to cut it to third man for a single
ticks him up with one aimed at the ribs, defended to leg
misses out on a fullish delivery on the pads, beaten by the pace
short, and helped away to third man for a single
driven in the air, shouts of "catch it", but he gets it wide of mid-off, and gets four
short of a length on the off, steps back and cuts it straight to point
angling in towards middle and of, gets forward and defends it towards extra cover
short of a length on middle, drops it towards midwicket from the crease
rocks on the back foot and defends it into the off side
short and he gets into position early to step back and punch it through extra cover for a couple of runs, spun away but he handled it well
sliding it towards middle, tickles it towards short fine
back of a length and guided down to third man for a single
stays short of a length, but closer to the stumps, defended to cover
slower ball, around off, kicks at him, Taylor gets the bottom hand off and keeps it down
Keirn Pollar dives to his left at backward point and saves four. It was cut away powerfully, and Pollard does well
drops this shortish delivery into the covers and gets a single
drops towards mid-on and runs, there is a collision between Taylor and Sammy as Taylor goes for the run and Sammy for the ball. In the end both are safe
turn for Benn, beats Taibu, Fletcher doesn't collect cleanly
tossed up, defended towards cover
beaten outside off, nicely flighted and just a hint of turn beating the bat
stretches forward and defends to cover
flighted outside off, pushed to cover off the front foot
turn there again, beats a tentative poke outside off, Fletcher is alert now, Maiden over
back of a length, pushed towards cover, Gayle's dive keeps them in their crease
deflected off the pad, and gets a single to fine leg
powerfully square-driven, and Pollard is good at backward point again
back of a length, around off, no room, defended to cover
cut in front of square, sweeper-cover is in place
bunts a back-of-a-length delivery to wide of mid-on, comes through for one
flighted around off, defended into the off side
nice cover-drive, with the spin, on the up, and just guided between mid-off and extra cover, all timing and placement
pushes a fullish delivery down to long-on for one
slows this one down, Taibu gets a thickish edge but they come through for a sharp single to short third man
presses forward and pats this one back to Benn
shortish outside off, and left alone
stays on target, no room, short-of-driving length, and pushed back to the bowler
turns this one wide of square leg and takes a single
Sammy stays on the same short-of-driving length, and Taylor pushes it back to him
slower ball, fuller too, and easily pushed down to long-on for one
pinches a single having hit it straight to mid-off, Taibu is lightning quick
another slower delivery, gets an inside edge onto the pad
bunts this one towards backward point and hares through for one again
steps out of the crease, Benn pulls the length back, and he ends up defending it
pushes an overpitched delivery down to long-on
driven with an open face, straight to Pollard at backward point
another nice-looking drive, gets a single to sweeper-cover
overpitched, driven down the ground, gets a single
worked off the pads, Deonaraine makes a nice diving save at square leg, saves one for West Indies
pitched up, driven down the ground, but finds mid-off
into the pads, and helped away towards fine leg
length ball outside off, played back to the bowler
looks to take a single to cover, but Gayle runs in quickly and Taibu decides against the run
looks to cut, but can't get it past Pollard at backward point
full ball, driven down the ground for a single
steals a single after hitting it just to the left of Gayle at cover
flat delivery, on middle and leg, pushed down the ground for one
superb shot! flighted outside off, Taibu goes inside-out, lovely drive with the high elbow, and gets enough height to clear Gayle
flatter and faster, turned to midwicket
comes forward and smothers this one
nice shot by Taylor, sees the mid-on is up and goes over him. Doesn't get the sweetest of connection, but enough to clear Barath
looks to pull a shortish delivery and misses, wasn't short enough for the shot
goes back to his length, not drivable, just outside off, and defended towards cover
offcutter, gets an inside edge, but it misses the leg stump
runs this one down to third man for an easy single
full delivery, and it's hit towards the three-fourths mid-on, and gets him a single
tossed up around off, presses forward and defends
shorter, pushed down the ground without fuss
overpitched on the pads, and flicked away for a single
worked away off the pads, wide of midwicket, and gets two
fullish, leg-sidish, pushed down the ground for one
more offish this time, and Taibu hits it back to him, one bounce
turn for him, beats Taylor's attempt to flick it
this time he connects with the flick but can't beat midwicket
poor delivery but Bernard makes a superb diving save at long leg, saving two runs for his team, it was short and into the pads, and was pulled away fine
turn for Gayle again, beats him and appeals for leg-before, perhaps turning down the leg side
he has given him this time! beats him with the offbreak again, and beats Taylor on the flick. The ball looks good to hit the stumps, but seems to have hit him outside off
full delivery, driven to sweeper-cover for one
turn for Miller, Matsinkeyeri hangs his bat outside off and is beaten
tip-and-run here, just drops it at his feet and comes through for one
into the pads, pushed back to the bowler
fuller, outside off, and hit straight to Gayle at cover
short delivery, looks to turn it to leg, but it turns away from him, and he has to change his shot, and defends it back to the bowler
flat, fast outside off, defended back to the bowler
slows this one down, defended back to him, "Well done skippy," says Fletcher
turning in again, played to midwicket
overpitched, and pushes this one down to long-on
opens the face late, and gets a single to short third
turn for Gayle again, beats him but doesn't go for the appeal because it is sliding down the leg side
paddles this one from in front of the stumps, and over the keeper, and gets a couple
moves across, outside the line, and sweeps it to square leg
full ball, played with an open face towards point
turn again, beats him outside off, Matsinkeyeri is tentative outside off
premeditated sweep, and he is beaten again
soft dismissal but the pressure was on for Matsinkeyeri! looks to push a short delivery into the covers, but it doesn't quite come on and he hits it straight to Gayle at short cover. Easy catch
turns this one to leg, from in front of the stumps, and gets a single
floats this one outside off, defended towards short cover
pushes down the ground to get off the mark
wants a single into the leg side, but can't beat midwicket
poor delivery, short, turning down the leg side, and helped away fine of short fine leg for a couple
sharp turn this time, gets a long way forward and outside the line to negotiate the delivery
more turn fro Miller but this starts outside off and is left alone
gets a thick outside edge, but it is along the ground and they get a single to point
thrown up wide, Taibu shuffles across and drives square, wide of sweeper-cover
Taibu is gone! Big wicket! The most experienced Zimbabwean gone. He premeditates the sweep, doesn't get to the pitch of it, and gets a tame top edge to short fine leg
flat delivery, angling into him, defended to midwicket
tossed up around off, defended again
flat outside off, pushed to short cover
nicely tossed up outside off, defended to cover
yorks him with this quick delivery, hit back to the bowler
flighted outside off, and pushed to cover
Lamb wants a single but it is hit straight to backward point, and he dives back in to make his ground
into the pads, and turned away for the first run of the over
nicely hit, that will take some pressure off Zimbabwe. Short, and he cuts this in front of square, sweet timing there and it goes past cover
flat but fuller, defended to cover
tossed up around off, pushed to cover
straighter but more flight on it, Elton stays in the crease and defends
angled into the pads, and hit back to the bowler
this time clears the front leg and pushes this down to long-on for one
flat delivery, pushed back to the bowler
flighted around off, defended back to the bowler
tossed up outside off again, doesn't get it away
plays this one with an open face, gets a single to wide of cover

full, fast, straight, big lbw shout, not given. replays show it hit him on the foot on the full and in front of the stumps. Perhaps Umpire Duncan reckoned an inside edge, it didn't seem so in the replay, though
pushed to mid-on
full outside off, driven down to long-off
tossed up outside off, defended to cover
nice shot, Miller drops this one short, and Elton rocks back, makes room, and cuts it past point
flights this one around off, and is driven down the ground
into the pads, and pushed down to long-on
full and fast, played back to Gayle
drags this flighted delivery from outside off, gets a single to wide long-on
plays a shortish delivery to backward point
looks to turn this to leg, is beaten by the turn
full toss, doesn't take advantage and hits it back to the bowler
comes forward and gets this one down to long-on for one
flat, around off, defended back to him
beats him sharp turn just outside off
this is slightly shorter, and he is cut away for a single
turns this off the pads, with soft hands, no man inside the circle on the leg side, gets two
short and wide, cut away to sweeper-cover for one
into the pads, and he gets a single down to long-on
good take by Fletcher down the leg side, but it's a wide nonetheless
goes for a single to long-on, but can't get it wide enough of Gayle
looks for another single to long-on, but hits too close to midwicket this time
tossed up outside off, creates a bat-pad gap, gets an inside edge that somehow evades the leg stump
shorter, and hit to sweeper-cover for one
plays with the turn, can't get it past midwicket
full and fast outside off, guided down to third man
full and wide outside off, doesn't connect well on the drive, gets the inside half of  the bat, back to the bowler

a run-out possibility, hit slightly wide of midwicket, Elton wants the run, Lamb doesn't. Elton goes back from half way up the pitch but makes it back because it is hit to the right of Miller and he has to get around
defended back to Roach
length ball outside off, doesn't make good connection on the drive again
angled into the pads, and helped away towards fine leg
holds its line outside off, and beats his poke
whipped from around off and middle, gets a single
turning into him, and he gets it wide of midwicket for a single
looks to whip it from outside off, doesn't turn in, and gets a thick edge that goes for two
pushes with the turn, can't beat midwicket
shorter, looks to get a single to long-on, can't beat midwicket
nicely tossed up, under 50 miles an hour, played back to the bowler
nicely bowled outside off, holds its line, and also perhaps beats him for the pace, 89mph
fuller outside off, driven one bounce to cover
Miller does superbly at midwicket, full-length dive to his left and that causes misunderstanding, and a dot ball. The sparse crowd comes to life
back of a length, outside off, defended to cover
bunts this one to wide of cover and gets a single
looks to help it into the leg side, trying to use Roach's pace, but finds midwicket
worked off the pads for a single to wide of square leg
fuller, driven down the ground, gets a single
looks to play it towards fine leg but is beaten by the offbreak
arm ball, flat outside off, beats his outside edge
wants a single to short third but Miller is quick and Lamb is sent back
into the pads and helped away to fine leg for one
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, played towards backward point
short and wide, cut away in front of square, gets a couple to wide of sweeper-cover
fuller ball, driven down the ground, gets a single

Pollard gets an edge and Fletcher is late to dive to his right. Short and wide delivery, gets an edge, and it goes about six inches wide of Fletcher's outstretched single-gloved attempt. Counts as a drop
stays low and bounces in front of keeper, Fletcher does well this time
turned to midwicket , with the angle
into the pads, turned away to short fine
tossed up, driven down the ground, gets a single
straighter one outside off, gets the outside half of the bat
worked off the pads, gets a single to deepmidwicket
into the pads, and turned around the corner
length delivery wide of off, driven to sweeper-cover
looks to drive down the ground, is beaten by the angle, gets an inside edge onto the pads
angled into the pads, is late into the shot and the ball rolls along off the pad
wide outside off, and hit to deep point for one

walks down the track, plays straight to backward point and he sends Lamb back. Sammy shies at the stumps, misses the stumps, gives away an overthrow, but the fielder backing up throws wildly again, giving away another extra run
pushes a length delivery to wide of cover, gets a single
nicely bowled, flighted, angled in, pitching and turning away and beating him
slightly shorter but there is turn and bounce and he can't get it away
nicely tossed up outside off, pushed to cover
angled into the pads this time, and hit down the ground for one
flighted again, comes forward and defends
looks to whip it against the turn, ends up hitting it one bounce to Benn
short outside off, pushed to point
slower ball, 68mph, checks the shot, gets a single to sweeper-cover
superb full-length dive off his own bowling across the length of the pitch to save one run
goes wide of off, and gets just too wide
into the pads, clipped towards fine leg for one
would have been wide had he not slashed at it, but he makes good connection and goes over point, getting four runs, good shot
nicely bowled slower delivery, beats him outside off, Fletcher does well to collect it on the second bounce
premeditated paddle, is beaten, but the lbw is not given because it is turning across the stumps
shapes up for the big inside-out, but aborts the shot, there isn't enough room
cramps him up again, pitching outside leg and turning, defended to cover
lovely shot, clears the front leg a touch, gets the room, and lofts it sweetly over mid-off
and he hits where the fielder was removed from! sweeps, gets a semi-top-edge but clears the square leg-side field, smart batting
sweeps again, can't find the gap between fine leg and square leg in the circle
back of a length, around off, plays with soft hands, gets a single to mid-on
tip-and-run again, wide of mid-on this time
goes for the big hit down the ground, doesn't connect well, gets a single to wide of mid-off
length delivery outside off, doesn't go for the big hit, plays it to short cover
stays low and beats his attempted hit down the ground
bunts it to midwicket and scampers through for one
looks to cramp him up but bowls way down the leg side. A piece of paper flew across just as he bowled
another big wide down the leg side, no paper flew this time
on target this time, tries to to make room but can't get enough space
makes room, takes it from middle but hits it one bounce to cover
the leg-line works for Miller! A frustrated Lamb goes for the big sweep and top-edges it, and Miller holds on to the skier
Elton plays another nice inside-out shot, clears the front leg to make room and chips over extra cover
50 for Elton! worked around the corner off the pads, valuable fifty and a smartly played innings
helps this one to short fine but Elton sends Cremer back. perhaps he wants more of strike in the Powerplay

big wicket at this time of the game! Elton is gone, the man who could hit the quick runs in the end. Goes for the big shot over the covers, the length is right to go for it, but it's that slight extra pace for Roach and he ends up lobbing it to cover-point
tucks him up with a shorter delivery, turns it to fine leg for one
runs this one down to third man, gets a single
another dab to third man, another single
edged away for four, fuller delivery, looks for the third-man single but gets a fine edge. Zimbabwe won't mind them
nice yorker, aimed for the toe, 89mph, does well to keep it out
swept fine, can't get it past short fine, sent back by Cremer
comes down the track, doesn't get close to the pitch of it, defends
sweeps, gets a single to long leg
gets a leading edge as he looks to turn this to leg, one bounce to point
sweeps, but this is not the sweeping length and he is beaten by the turn and the angle
sweeps again, misses again, but gets a leg bye this time
goes for the big slash outside off, gets an inside edge, one bounce to the keeper
makes room, goes for another big shot, mis-hits, and just about chips over the infield
shortish, chops it to short third and gets a single
full delivery, gets big turn and beats his attempt at the inside-out shot
fast and into the block hole, another dot
hits a full delivery down to long-off for one
goes for the reverse-sweep, gets just a single to short third man
steps out, hits down the ground for one
that's a lovely shot, makes room as he comes down the track, gets under the delivery and lofts him straight, dead straight, into the sight screen
sweeps, and misses
steps outside the crease again, places into the on side, soft hands, and they scamper through for two
bowled him! Cremer makes room again, but misses the cut shot, this one pitches outside leg, and turns and takes the leg stump
turns this one to midwicket for one
length ball around off, can;t do much with it, hits it back to the bowler
bowled him! walks down the track and misses by a mile, and the leg stump is out of the ground. Roach kisses the badge on his short
full and fast, misses the off stump, looks for a bye but is sent back and rightly so
Zimbabwe's innings is over! gets a leading edge one bounce to Gayle at cover. He wants a single but is sent back and is late in going back, and is found short

inn2.comm: and Gayle goes after him first ball, gets a thick edge, which just clears point
gets stuck into this one, though, straight down the ground, not much power, just timing that takes it into the sight screen
hits thid down the ground, gets a single to long-on
beaten by the turn - there is some break here for Utseya, but it's turning down the leg
dabs this to short third
short and flat, and hit down the ground for one
full, into the pads, driven down to long-on for one
defended towards short midwicket
flat into the pads, stays low, played to square leg, pretty crowded leg-side field
nicely tossed up around off, defended to the bowler
turning into the pads, played along the ground to short midwicket. Ray gives Gayle a dirty look, what a guy
nicely tossed up outside off, presses forward and defends
short, cut away, but Mpofu does well at backward point
angled into the pads, played towards midwicket
half-tracker and punished! Barath has a lot of time to rock back and pull him over leg-side infield
sharp single to short fine, Chigumbura does well to swoop on and let go, misses the stumps by inches, would have made for interesting replays had he hit
short, turns and stays low, defeating the attempted big shot from Gayle, getting the bottom part of the bat
Matsinkeyeri has dropped a sitter at backward square leg in the circle! Barath looks to pull but this is not short and skids on, the top edge flies to the fielder who lets it out of his hands
uppishly played towards short midwicket, bounces in front
steps out, is beaten in the flight, but goes through with the shot, gets enough bat on it to clear the cover field
flat around off, patted back to the bowler
flighted outside off, Gayle presses forward and defends
pushed down the ground, gets a single to long-on
short, and crashed away through the covers. Can't bowl freebies to Gayle
into the pads, patted towards midwicket
steps out of the crease, Utseya fires it into the pads, Gayle defends
presses all the way forward and defends
gets another big stride in and defends
steps out again, doesn't get close to the ball, still manages to hit it down the ground and along the ground, and gets a single
slightly short, stops on him, goes uppishly towards short midwicket, just straight enough of him, gets him a single
appeal for lbw, but there is no turn, hence it is going down the leg side
angled into the pads, turned away to midwicket
pins him on the crease again with a ball angled into the pads
goes for the sweep, is beaten, but all's safe
flat into the pads again, turned away to short fine
looks to sweep, Utseya bowls it real slow, under 50 miles an hour, Gayle's sweep becomes a one-handed attempt, and he misses and is hit in the pad
short, into the body, and pulled away handsomely, and the square fielder on the leg side is too straight
steps out of the crease, and defends
short, and gives him enough width here, and he has bludgeoned this through point. Superb shot
lovely shot! steps out, makes room, doesn't care about the power, just makes sure he goes over mid-off and not towards long-on, the free swing gives him enough power to clear the long-off fence
looks to turn it to leg, gets a leading edge and he scampers through for two
edged to short of slip, Price has something to say to the slip fielder, who goes wider
around off, defended towards cover

superb arm ball from Price! and he has given him! Barath sees a short delivery, opens up for the cut but it follows him with the arm and skids onto him, but the replays show it hit him outside the line of off
presses forward and defends the first ball he faces
strays down the leg side, gets a glove on the attempted sweep, will get him a single
flat delivery, around off, punched to cover
starts off with an accurate delivery, around off, just back of a length, Bernard defends
gets too far across looking to turn it to leg, Mpofu doesn't get the lbw decision because it is sliding down the leg side
presses forward and defends a length delivery back to the bowler
on target again, doesn't give him driving length, doesn't give him room to free arms. It's defended back to the bowler
plays with an open face, can't get it past point
starts off with a maiden, Bernard plays across the line of a straightish delivery, and is hit on the pad outside the line of off
turning into the pads, lets it hit the pad, going down the leg side anyway
stretches forward and defends it back to Price
looks to cut but it is too full for the shot. The bat, though, comes down in time. price smiles and stares at Gayle
pushes a flat delivery down to long-on for one

Taibu you little beauty! Price bowls full and wide down the leg side, Bernard overbalances as he misses it, and Taibu makes a clean collection and whips the bails off in a flash, and leaps up and down towards Price as they celebrate
pure Chanders! moves a long way across, and gives it the sweetest part of the bat when he defends
straighter delivery outside off, and beats Chanders's defensive shot
nicely bowled, around leg, turning away a touch, defended back to the bowler, a sort of leading edge
defends with an open face, towards short third
stretches forward and defends
gets the big front foot down and works it off his pads
big appeal for lbw, pitches off, turns away and beats him and hits him on the back leg, missing off
flat into the pads, played towards midwicket
full, almost yorks him, played back to the bowler
flatter and shorter, pushed to long-on for one
nicely played, moves across to get close to the line, and guides it through covers, against the spin, just using the wrists and the open face
reverse-sweep, he has got a liking for the shot of late, connects well but can't get it past short third
cuts this one wide enough of point to get a single
gets a big stride in and defends
short, hits it down the ground, can't beat mid-off
into the pads, played to midwicket
stops at him, short, and turns away, Chanders keeps it down
looks to hit another short ball down the ground, can't get it past midwicket
straight delivery, but turned straight to short fine leg
another maiden, hits a flighted delivery back to the bowler
in the channel around off, defended to cover
full delivery, guided towards point for a quick single
flighted around off, played to cover
stays low and skids on, and Chanderpaul gets the bat down just in nick of time
into the pads, Chanderpaul misses
another skiddy delivery, Chanderpaul gets bat down in time again, Taibu is excited, is jumping up and down, real contest on
turn, bounce, beaten! pitches off, angling in, and then leaves him, Taibu collects it throat-high
slower, flighted, and beats him again
full, into the pads, played to midwicket
a shot of frustration, looks to sweep, misses, ball sliding down leg
comes forward, plays it with soft hands, and guides it past slip
another nice offbreak, pitches off, and leaves him, seven runs in last five overs
swept one-handed, can't get it past short fine

big, big shout, Gayle sweeps again, and is beateb. Ball pitches middle, turns towards off, and the only reason he is not given could be that Gayle is a big man and must have been way down the wicket, and the ball is turning a lot
flat delivery around off, played to cover
big offbreak, beats him again
driven down to long-on for one
flat delivery around off, defended back to the bowler
nicely played, uses Lamb's pace to guide it past short third
slower through the air, and the ball grips and breaks away, and beats him
goes straighter, doesn't turn much this time, defended back to the bowler
nice shot, too straight, and flicks it past short fine to get two
presses forward and defends a flat delivery
the first poor delivery in ages, fired down the leg side, Taibu can't get around in time, five wides
pushes a length delivery to cover
nicely guided away between point and cover, gets a single
looks to cut but it doesn't come on, ends up playing it to cover
turns away a fullish delivery to short fine leg
leading edge as he looks to turn it to leg. it lands safely towards point
stops and turns at him, nice hands from Chanders to keep it down
plays this to wide of midwicket and comes through for one
doesn't turn much, ends up playing outside the line, gets an inside edge onto the pad
skiddy delivery outside off, hurries him into the shot, one bounce to the bowler
stretches forward and defends to cover
comes down the track, comes close to the pitch of the ball, and pushes it to long-off for one
fast and flat, beats Gayle, off the pad to slip where Price doesn't catch it. The body language of the bowler suggests there might have been an edge, the replays suggest otherwise
turned away around the corner for a single
full, on the pads, swept away for a single
into the pads again, turned away to midwicket
gets the outside half of the bat as he turns the bat too early, it's safe towards point
four valuable leg-byes for West Indies, pitches outside leg, straightens and takes a big chunk of the pad on the way through
uses his feet, doesn't go through with the shot and pushes it back to the bowler
is beaten on the defensive shot outside off as the ball doesn't turn this time, but it must have hit him outside off
gets a stride in and pats it back to the bowler
presses forward to cover the spin and then plays it back to the bowler
big offbreak and Gayle keeps the bat close to his pad and misses by a long way
turned into the square leg region to get to his fifty, acknowledges not extravagantly the applause from the crowd
short delivery, can't get it past point
this short ball he punches down the ground for one
played with the spin, wide of mid-on, gets a single
big big stride, and defended
full, flighted around leg, turning away, Taibu had a difficult difficult chance of stumping him here, couldn't collect it cleanly
turned to midwicket
flatter delivery, hurries him into the shot, defended back
turned around the corner, can't beat short fine leg
pushed down the ground, gets a single
comes right forward to defend this one
strays too straight, hit down to long-on for one
opens the face late, soft hands too, gets it past slip for one, along the ground
comes forward, turns it around the front leg, gets a single

he has finally got him! pitches leg, turns away, beats him, hits him in the back leg, in front of off, but just over the knee roll, height could have been the only issue, but Umpire Duncan is sure enough
turning in big, beats him, gets the pad in the way
this is a big miss by Taibu! dips on Gayle as he drives, misses, the ball turns down the leg side as Gayle loses balance, and again Taibu doesn't make a clean collection
flighted around off, and he drives down the ground for a single
flighted around off, defended
throws it up again, breaks away after pitching off, defended
beats him outside off, turn and bounce again, Fletcher stays inside the line
watchfully defends off the front foot
gets an inside edge as this one doesn't turn, along the ground to short fine
overpitched, easy single down the ground
stays low, Fletcher is back, Zim are excited, gets the bat down in time
shout for lbw as he sweeps, gets a bottom edge
looks to cut a fullish delivery, manages to keep it out
big stride outside off, defended
comes forward, uses soft hands to turn it away to square leg
beautifully bowled wrong'un! nicely flighted outside off, Fletcher is drawn into the drive, and the googly finds its way through the big bat-pad gap, lovely spin bowling
and he greets Cremer by pulling the first ball he faces, slightly short and he jumps on it, gets a couple
beautiful inside-out drive, overpitched delivery but it needs putting away and he plays a nice drive against the spin, wide of long-off, gets two
charges down the track and hits this one back to Cremer, on the bounce
presses forward and defends it back to the bowler
short, into the pads, gets a single wide of midwicket
forward defensive, correct shot, right under his eyes
pushes down the ground, but it stops on him, and goes uppishly but wide enough of the bowler
full and fast into the pads, misses out
big wide down the leg side, Taibu does well to get his pads around
overpitched outside off, can't get it past extra cover
stays back to a skidder, gets bat down in time
gives him the charge, gets to the pitch of the ball, and drives it handsomely down the ground
overpitched on the pads, whipped away to midwicket for one
tossed up outside off, watchfully defended
tossed up outside off, gets close to the pitch and plays it to cover
gets right to the pitch again and drives it down to long-off
short ball, stays low, he still manges to get under it, and pulls over midwicket, a distinct Chanderpaul-like look to that shot
flighted around off, defended towards backward point
short delivery, pushed down the ground for one
wide down the leg side again
still into the pads, and played down the ground for an easy single
nicely tossed up, around leg, but it's slower through the air, and he defends
defends a fullish delivery with an open face
pushed down the ground, gets a single to long-off
turn and bounce, but Deonariane pushes forward, gets outside the line and offers his pad
shapes up for the pull, but the turn and bounce defeat him, it lobs up towards midwicket but falls short
opens the face on it, can't get it past short third man
breaking into him, turned away towards midwicket
flatter straighter delivery, played towards cover
left alone outside off
thick edge as he pushes at it outside off, gets a single
length ball, outside off, defends with an open face, sent back by Gayle
goes for the cut and misses, was there for the taking. Still there is more for the taking as he has over-stepped
and he ducks into a bouncer! off a free hit! what a bizarre turn of events
length delivery outside off, covers his stumps and leaves it alone
pushes at it with an open face, gets it past cover for a single
overpitched, gets a single to long-off
looks for a single on the on side, can't get it past midwicket
almost yorks him with a full delivery, played back to the bowler
sweeps from in front of the stumps, gets a single
googly, stays back and plays it back to the bowler
turned away off the pads, to short fine leg
slower ball on the pads, and helped away for an easy single
runs this one down to third man for a single
hit back powerfully, Elton does well to field it in his followthrough
flicked away off the pads, into the gap between fine leg and deep midwicket, gets a ciuple
pulled away even as he takes his eyes off it, keeps it along the ground, gets a single to fine leg
short and wide, cut away to deep point, would have been wide had he left it alone
turning into the pads, played towards midwicket
stays back to a fullish delivery, defends it back to Ray
gives it some air this time, defended again
big big shout from Price, and optimistic too as this is turning too much
flighted generously again, Deonaraine comes forward and pushes it into the covers
wide down the leg side
flat, into the stumps, and pushed to midwicket
big offbreak straight away and beats his defensive shot, Taibu disturbs the bails but Deonaraine is back in
big big optimistic shout for lbw, and again it is turning too much
defended with an open face towards point
overpitched, can't get it past extra cover
and again he can't get an overpitched delivery past extra cover
shoulders arms to one headed down the leg side
gets a leading edge as he looks to turn it to on, it lands safe
looks to turn it to leg, finds midwicket
full delivery, pushed down the ground for a single
hit powerfully towards long-off, gets a single
overpitched and pushed down to long-on for one
flipper, and he cuts it to sweeper-cover
short, turning away, hit down to long-off
strays down the leg side, another wide
presses forward and gets an inside edge onto the pad
defends this offbreak towards cover
overpitched, pushed to long-on, Gayle still not trying big shots
looks to tip and run, but has hit a bit too strongly to cover
comes forward and opens the face on it, plays it to short third man
Gayle still keeps the big shots away, pushes a full delivery to long-of

finally, finally, the shackles are broken, Deonaraine charges down, makes good ground and turns this into a half-volley, and lofts it straight, clean and flat - first boundary off the bat since the seventh over
flatter delivery, guided to short third
slog sweep, another big shot, neatly connected, over midwicket, gets four, Deonaraine has brought the crowd alive
presses forward and defends
short and wide, cut away to deep point
short again, but no room this time, punched straight to point
gives him width this time, cut away in front of square, enough space created between the shot and the sweeper-cover for them to come back for two
slower ball, stays in the crease and pats it to midwicket
fuller, but too wide of off stump, pressure easing off here
nice nice shot, unorthodox but effective, leans back and lofts this over extra cover off the back foot, four more valuable runs
nearly chopped on, stays low and takes the bottom edge on the pull, stays clear of the leg stump
turns this off the pads, gets a single to wide of short fine
lovely inside-out chip shot, gets to the pitch and then opens the face and plays towards wide long-off; Masakadza doesn't get his angles right at long-off and concedes a boundary
full delivery, pushed to long-off for one
short, punched down the ground for a single
pitches leg, turns towards off, defended with an open face
charges down, makes this into a full toss, drives powerfully and straight, Masakadza at long-off does well to dive to his left and keeps them down to one
wide down the leg side, Zimbabwe can do without those
high full toss, wide too, hit powerfully towards sweeper-cover, not called a no-ball - touch and go call
gets the inside half of the bat on the drive, drags it from wide outside off to get a single to long-on
short, pulled away to deep square leg for a single
short, into the body, nicely tucked away to fine of fine leg, gets a couple
another wide down the leg side, that makes it 14 runs in wides so far
lovely shot, and that's 81 balls between boundaries for Gayle! gets close to the ball and chips it over extra cover, high elbow, all timing
and he goes over extra cover again, this time it's an old-fashioned biff, clears the front leg and just goes boom, one bounce into the fence
comes forward and defends Cremer
shorter, worked away towards fine leg, gets a single
looks for a single but Cremer dives full length to left and fields
what a wonderful reverse-sweep, through point, and to say that he has played a remarkably restrainful innings

one big shot too many! Cremer has got the big wicket! Gayle charges down the wicket, doesn't get close to the pitch of the ball, ends up swinging outside the line and is bowled, but it's been a superb knock on a testing wicket
presses forward and guides a legbreak to short third man
lovely shot. slightly short, and he punches it through covers, into the gap more importantly, and gets the valuable boundary
short, into the body, played to midwicket
gets away with one down the leg side, umpire Duncan reckons it might have taken the pad on the way
flat, hurries him into a shot straight to cover
short and wide, and cut away to sweeper-cover
flighted around off, defended, Utseya is done
nicely done, pushes forward and guides it to wide of short third man for a single
clean clean strike, this looked like just a chip, and the flick of the wrist and the heavy bat and the sweet connection take it over long-on for a six
this time he keeps it along the ground, gets a single
gets the stride in and plays the forward-defensive
driven against the spin, can;t get it past extra cover
shorter delivery, works it to short fine leg, and reaches a mature, timely half-century, and gets a generous applause from his home crowd. Truly deserved too
that must have slipped out of the hand, full toss into the pads and lofted over the leg-side field
Deonarine tips and runs and the crowd is cheering even the singles

he has hit it into the lap of long-on, poor shot! long-on is one of the three fielders outside and he has picked him. Gayle - in the players' lobby, with the pads still on - has a furious look on his face. Don't go anywhere near the skipper, boys!
big big shout right away, but the big turn saves Sammy
Sammy pushes down to long-on for a single
pitched outside leg, turning towards middle, defended
Sammy stays back to play a fullish delivery, arms go up in the air, Ray walks towards the batsman, smiles and stares, good drama
oh no another wide, down the leg side, this game would have been closer but for the wides
stays low, Sammy gets the bat down in time, this time Ray has an angry look on his face
into the pads, misses, can;t get leg-bye either
into the pads again, and flicked away to deep square leg; Ray has a word with Sammy as he takes the single
Deonarine looks to tip and run, but Sammy makes a good call of no as Mpofu is very quick at point
nicely played, good good shot, charges down the track, makes it into a half-volley, and then plays it straight down the ground, to the right of long-on, and comes back for two
and that's another extra, wide down the leg side
oh Sammy boy, he plays an irresponsible pull shot, gets the top edge that falls short of fine leg
short again, gets on top of this one, keeps it down, and gets Deonarine on strike
yorker, well bowled, dot ball
walks down the track, makes it into a low fulltoss, can't get it past extra cover
drilled down the ground, a fumble by Elton at long-on gives them the second
slower ball, bunted into the covers, and Sammy backs away a long way and makes sure Deonarine is on strike to face the next over

Deonarine playes another lovely shot, steps out and chips it straight down the ground, over mid-off, the idea is to clear the infield and not the ground, and he does that well, and despite a Mastinkeyeri dive the ball reaches the rope
full delivery, hit powerfully, but straight to mid-off
Deonarine doesn't want any glorious finish, he pushes this down to long-on, takes a single
defends a length ball back to Price
that's it, West Indies have levelled the series with a straight shot, straight of mid-off, and turns back towards the pavilion
